@startuml
title Viaverse Search / SEO / Growth — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Next.js Client\nSearch screen\nFeed\nSEO pages" as Client
component "API Gateway / Web BFF\nSearch API\nSEO route API" as BFF
component "SearchController\nSeoController\nGrowthController" as Controller
component "Search Use Cases\nSearch\nIndexEntity\nGenerateSeoPage\nTrackSearchEvent" as UseCases
component "Search Policies\nprivacy gates\nranking gates\nsponsored constraints\nlocalization" as Policies
component "Ports\nSearchIndexPort\nTrustSignalPort\nAiIntentPort\nAnalyticsPort\nSeoRepo\nOutboxPort" as Ports
database "OpenSearch\npublic projections\ngeo/full-text\nfacets" as OpenSearch
component "AI intent/category service\nquery understanding\nsuggestions" as AI
component "analytics-service\nimpressions\nclicks\nconversion funnel" as Analytics
database "PostgreSQL\nseo_page\nsearch_config\nexperiment" as DB
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nEntityPublished\nSearchPerformed\nSeoPageUpdated" as Kafka
component "CDN / Next.js SSR\nSEO pages\nsitemap\nschema.org" as CDN

Client --> BFF : HTTPS
BFF --> Controller : REST/SSR
Controller --> UseCases : command/query
UseCases --> Policies : validate/rank
Policies --> Ports : ports
Ports --> OpenSearch : query/index
Ports --> AI : intent
Ports --> Analytics : events
Ports --> DB : SEO/config
UseCases --> Kafka : events
UseCases --> CDN : publish SEO/sitemap
Kafka ..> UseCases : index events

note bottom
SEO pages are generated only from public/approved projections.
Search-service must not leak private request details or exact addresses.
end note
@enduml
